WEBVTT

00:29.197 --> 00:31.358
Woman on TV:
The details are unclear,

00:31.365 --> 00:34.528
but information continues to
pour in on this shocking story.

00:34.535 --> 00:37.242
What we do know is that...

00:37.246 --> 00:38.452
You ready?

00:38.456 --> 00:41.744
[Woman speaking indistinctly
on TV]

00:41.751 --> 00:44.584
Look at me.

00:44.587 --> 00:46.669
I'm sorry.

00:46.672 --> 00:49.709
Sometimes things
just don't work out.

00:50.134 --> 00:51.465
Are we staying for good
this time?

00:51.469 --> 00:52.629
Yes.

00:52.637 --> 00:55.595
You'll see all your friends,
stay in the same school.

00:55.598 --> 00:57.839
It'll be just like
it used to be.

00:57.850 --> 01:01.308
Is the real reason we're staying
'cause that guy's dead?

01:01.312 --> 01:02.802
The one you arrested.

01:02.813 --> 01:04.519
In breaking news tonight,
alone gunman

01:04.524 --> 01:06.264
opened ﬁre
outside the city jail

01:06.275 --> 01:09.767
while police were transporting
Councilman Darren Richmond.

01:09.779 --> 01:12.441
[ Gunshot, crowd screaming] Eyewitnesses
have described the shooter as a while male,

01:12.448 --> 01:14.814
but other details
remain unclear

01:14.825 --> 01:17.487
As information continues
to pour in on this story,

01:17.495 --> 01:18.826
we will keep you informed.

01:18.829 --> 01:20.785
[Siren wailing]

01:27.046 --> 01:28.252
We're gonna try to take him.

01:28.256 --> 01:30.167
Keep moving, keep moving!

01:30.174 --> 01:32.290
What's happening?

01:32.301 --> 01:34.587
What's happening?

01:34.595 --> 01:36.335
Man: He's in cardiac arrest.
Code blue.

01:36.347 --> 01:37.678
Start compressions.

01:37.682 --> 01:39.889
Come on, pick him up.
Get him up, get him up.

01:42.353 --> 01:44.810
Jamie:
Somebody get the key!

01:44.814 --> 01:46.930
Take off his cuffs!

01:46.941 --> 01:48.522
Move, move!

01:48.526 --> 01:50.357
Come on! Move!

01:50.361 --> 01:52.898
All right, on 3. Up on 3.
1, 2, 3.

01:54.865 --> 01:57.026
Stay with compressions.

01:57.034 --> 01:58.149
Let's go. Move.

01:58.160 --> 01:59.320
Put him inside.
Get him inside.

01:59.328 --> 02:01.910
I'm going with him!

02:01.914 --> 02:04.121
[Grunting]

02:04.125 --> 02:05.956
All right, we're clear!

02:05.960 --> 02:08.326
Go, go, go!

02:08.337 --> 02:10.419
[Siren wailing]

02:32.194 --> 02:34.321
[ Car door closes]

02:38.993 --> 02:40.153
Sarah.

02:40.161 --> 02:41.401
The photo...

02:41.412 --> 02:42.572
It was faked.

02:44.123 --> 02:45.533
I think...

02:46.292 --> 02:48.783
I think that Rosie's
killer is still out there.

03:22.703 --> 03:25.194
You know what this means...

03:25.206 --> 03:27.697
For the department...

03:27.708 --> 03:30.700
You, me. My God.

03:30.961 --> 03:33.168
What if Richmond's innocent?

03:33.172 --> 03:34.378
You don't know that.

03:39.428 --> 03:41.214
I'll talk to DA Niilson.
She trusts me.

03:41.222 --> 03:43.383
She knows I wouldn't go to her
if I didn't have to.

03:43.391 --> 03:44.972
What are you gonna say?

03:44.975 --> 03:47.136
That a photo putting Richmond
on the bridge

03:47.144 --> 03:49.260
the same night Rosie
was killed was faked?

03:49.271 --> 03:51.262
By a cop, no less?

03:51.273 --> 03:53.730
If somebody wanted Richmond
to take the fall that bad...

03:53.734 --> 03:55.520
It doesn't mean
he didn't do it!

04:01.701 --> 04:05.068
I mean, really,
what do you have?

04:05.079 --> 04:07.365
A phone call
in the middle of the night?

04:07.373 --> 04:08.704
So, we let it go?
Is that it?

04:08.708 --> 04:10.244
I don't believe this!

04:12.044 --> 04:13.659
I shouldn't have come here.

04:13.671 --> 04:16.162
Look, sit!
Just... just sit.

04:21.470 --> 04:23.961
You and l are the only ones
who know about that photo.

04:23.973 --> 04:26.589
Let me look into it.
If I'm wrong, I'm wrong.

04:27.309 --> 04:30.801
Holder couldn't have done this
on his own.

04:30.813 --> 04:32.974
Who assigned him to homicide?

04:32.982 --> 04:36.065
I told you... his former
supervisor at county.

04:36.068 --> 04:37.274
What's his name?

04:38.237 --> 04:40.193
Gil Sloane.

04:40.197 --> 04:42.609
He's been a narc for 20 years,
Sheriff's Department.

04:43.409 --> 04:46.116
Lou, sheriff's department
oversees bridges and tunnels...

04:46.120 --> 04:48.156
The cameras on them.

04:48.164 --> 04:50.075
So now this is a conspiracy?

04:50.082 --> 04:53.165
The body in the campaign car
and now the photo?

04:53.169 --> 04:56.252
What if Richmond was set up
from the very beginning?

04:56.255 --> 04:59.088
What if Rosie was just part
of something bigger?

05:00.760 --> 05:03.297
It's just like the last time...

05:04.972 --> 05:06.963
...when you got sick.

05:10.519 --> 05:11.599
Sarah.

05:11.604 --> 05:13.686
Holder lied to me.

05:14.231 --> 05:15.482
All right.

05:17.318 --> 05:18.933
Go...

05:18.944 --> 05:21.151
You're going to do it anyways

05:22.740 --> 05:24.526
Let Jack sleep.

05:26.786 --> 05:29.243
Sarah?

05:31.123 --> 05:33.330
You be careful.

05:44.804 --> 05:48.012
[ Door opens ]

05:48.015 --> 05:50.301
[ Door closes]

05:51.769 --> 05:53.885
You mind?

06:02.321 --> 06:05.688
You got that Richmond photo
real quick, yo.

06:05.699 --> 06:07.906
Yeah.

06:07.910 --> 06:10.367
Your connects in county
paid off.

06:11.413 --> 06:13.153
I'm impressed.

06:15.459 --> 06:18.872
Guys like Richmond...
They never pay.

06:18.879 --> 06:21.370
It's about time.

06:21.382 --> 06:24.215
No doubt.

06:24.218 --> 06:26.209
You did good.

06:26.220 --> 06:29.178
You got a long career ahead...

06:29.181 --> 06:31.672
And all the shiny things
that come with it.

06:34.812 --> 06:37.178
[Cellphone rings]

06:37.189 --> 06:39.054
Holder.

06:43.153 --> 06:45.530
What?

06:45.948 --> 06:49.031
His moms, too?

06:49.034 --> 06:52.993
[Siren walls]

06:52.997 --> 06:54.783
Richmond's been shot.

07:02.381 --> 07:04.246
[ Police radio chatter]

07:10.556 --> 07:12.467
Officer: We got
Belko Royce's mother.

07:28.699 --> 07:30.439
Reporter: The assailant
has been identiﬁed

07:30.451 --> 07:32.316
as an employee of the Larsens.

07:32.620 --> 07:35.157
Belko Royce allegedly shot
Councilman Richmond

07:35.164 --> 07:37.951
as he was being transported
from police headquarters

07:37.958 --> 07:40.495
only hours after allegedly
gunning down...

07:40.502 --> 07:42.879
[Knock on door] his own
mother, Beverly Royce.

07:42.880 --> 07:44.495
The Councilman
was set to be transferred...

07:44.506 --> 07:45.791
Stan, there's someone
downstairs.

07:45.799 --> 07:47.460
from city holding
to county jail.

07:47.468 --> 07:49.584
The hospital
has yet to issue a statement...

07:49.595 --> 07:51.756
So, they got Belko
up at police headquarters,

07:51.764 --> 07:53.925
and they'll be transporting him
to county jail tomorrow night.

07:53.933 --> 07:56.390
[Sighs]

07:57.937 --> 08:00.053
Mr. Larsen, there's
something about Rosie's case

08:00.064 --> 08:00.928
that you should know.

08:00.940 --> 08:03.306
Maybe Mrs. Larsen
should be here, too.

08:03.317 --> 08:05.057
M—my wife's
not feeling well.

08:05.069 --> 08:07.151
Whatever you got to say,
just say it.

08:07.154 --> 08:13.571
Rosie met Richmond...
on an online service.

08:13.577 --> 08:16.865
An online service?
What kind of service?

08:16.872 --> 08:19.739
Beau Soleil.
It's an escort service.

08:21.085 --> 08:22.200
No.

08:22.211 --> 08:24.327
Sorry. I...

08:24.338 --> 08:27.421
I wanted to let you know
before the press does.

08:27.424 --> 08:29.460
[ Breathing heavily]

08:29.468 --> 08:32.301
You got that wrong.

08:33.889 --> 08:36.847
Look, l'll walk you downstairs.

08:38.102 --> 08:40.093
We got him, Mr. Larsen.

08:41.855 --> 08:43.811
We got him.

08:50.114 --> 08:52.651
Dr. Madigan: He sustained
a gunshot wound to the abdomen,

08:52.658 --> 08:54.944
the bullet pierced his stomach
and the gastric artery.

08:54.952 --> 08:56.408
Travers:
We're gonna need to contact

08:56.412 --> 08:57.401
Mr. Richmond's next of kin.

08:57.413 --> 08:59.995
He's got a sister in Boston,
Elyse.

08:59.999 --> 09:01.079
I put in a call.

09:01.083 --> 09:02.368
How is he?

09:02.376 --> 09:04.833
Well, if I can stop
the internal bleeding,

09:04.837 --> 09:06.828
he may still bleed out
from the incision.

09:06.839 --> 09:08.670
l have to go.

09:08.674 --> 09:10.039
What does that mean?

09:10.050 --> 09:10.425
What does that mean?

09:10.843 --> 09:13.630
That sister
should be on a plane... now.

09:18.726 --> 09:19.841
What the hell...

09:37.119 --> 09:38.655
[ Keys clacking]

09:42.499 --> 09:43.955
Seattle PD.

09:43.959 --> 09:47.372
Got a question about the cameras
on Desolation Bridge.

09:47.379 --> 09:49.335
Night of October 5th.

09:49.339 --> 09:51.295
[Clacking continues]

09:51.300 --> 09:53.382
[ Man speaking indistinctly]

09:53.385 --> 09:56.001
Cameras on that bridge have been
out of service since August.

09:56.638 --> 10:00.005
I need to get
printed confirmation.

10:00.017 --> 10:00.767
She's here.

10:00.768 --> 10:02.850
Wait here.

10:09.443 --> 10:13.311
[ Indistinct conversation ]

10:15.741 --> 10:18.608
Sorry for the inconvenience,
but you were misinformed.

10:18.619 --> 10:21.235
The cameras on Desolation Bridge
are in operation.

10:21.246 --> 10:23.032
He just said they were broken.

10:23.040 --> 10:25.372
New guy, not familiar
with the system.

10:25.375 --> 10:27.627
Bullshit.

10:28.253 --> 10:30.665
I got a call from your offices
earlier tonight,

10:30.672 --> 10:32.663
and that guy just said
the same thing.

10:32.674 --> 10:34.460
If you'd like me to call
your lieutenant,

10:34.468 --> 10:37.175
Detective Linden,
I'd be happy to.

10:37.513 --> 10:39.629
I never gave you my name.

10:40.349 --> 10:42.055
Why don't you take a seat?

10:42.059 --> 10:44.015
- I'll give him a call.
- Who were you talking to?

10:46.688 --> 10:48.644
[ Police radio chatter]

10:54.446 --> 10:57.062
Jack. Jack.
We got to go.

10:57.074 --> 10:58.109
What?
Shh.

10:58.117 --> 11:00.199
- Come on. Come on.
- Why?

11:00.202 --> 11:02.363
Get your shoes on.

11:02.371 --> 11:04.703
[Telephone ringing]

11:12.673 --> 11:14.288
Watch your fingers, baby.

11:25.686 --> 11:28.393
[ Engine turns over]

11:39.616 --> 11:41.607
There he is! There he is!
Jamie! Jamie!

11:41.618 --> 11:43.870
The Councilman is in surgery
right now.

11:43.871 --> 11:46.658
We don't know in what condition,
so I certainly can't comment on...

11:46.665 --> 11:48.530
Jamie, is Richmond
withdrawing from the race?

11:48.542 --> 11:51.079
We're talking about
a man's life here, Dan.

11:51.670 --> 11:53.285
I'm not speaking
on the election.

11:53.297 --> 11:55.333
Did he confess to murdering
Rosie Larsen?

11:55.340 --> 11:57.501
No. Because he didn't do it.

11:57.509 --> 11:58.840
When is he gonna...
We're finished.

11:58.844 --> 12:01.176
[ Indistinct shouting ]

12:03.307 --> 12:05.047
You should be ashamed!

12:06.727 --> 12:10.219
That's what I should have told
the parasites.

12:10.230 --> 12:12.607
[Sighs] Unbelievable.

12:12.608 --> 12:15.645
What?
What did they say?

12:15.652 --> 12:18.394
No, nothing.
No one's told me anything.

12:22.367 --> 12:26.201
He had an alibi.
He was with you.

12:26.205 --> 12:29.572
How do the police think
he did this?

12:32.669 --> 12:34.921
Any word
on Mr. Richmond's sister?

12:34.922 --> 12:36.787
Not yet.
She's on the East Coast.

12:36.798 --> 12:37.787
How is he?

12:37.799 --> 12:40.336
Is the Councilman
a religious man?

12:40.344 --> 12:41.629
Why?

12:41.637 --> 12:45.971
In case he'd want a pastor,
priest, or rabbi here...

12:45.974 --> 12:47.510
For last rites.

12:47.517 --> 12:49.803
Simply a cautionary measure.

12:49.811 --> 12:51.312
Let me know if you hear
from his sister.

12:51.313 --> 12:52.849
Well, what the hell
is going on?

12:52.856 --> 12:55.393
We've been waiting all night.
No one has told us anything.

12:55.400 --> 12:58.517
I'm sorry. You're gonna have to
wait for Dr. Madigan.

13:32.229 --> 13:34.015
You got your talking points,
Mr. Mayor?

13:34.022 --> 13:36.138
Press are here,
panties all in a twist.

13:37.776 --> 13:40.609
Critical condition,
still in surgery.

13:42.197 --> 13:45.064
I didn't want to win this way.

13:53.083 --> 13:55.415
Man on radio: The Richmond campaign
has not released a statement

13:55.419 --> 13:57.284
regarding
the Councilman 's condition.

13:57.796 --> 13:59.377
Are we going back to Regi's?

13:59.381 --> 14:01.167
No, she's still
in the San Juans.

14:02.050 --> 14:04.507
Then where are we going?

14:04.511 --> 14:07.218
The Councilman is said to be in
critical condition at this time.

14:07.222 --> 14:08.837
Are you hungry?

14:08.849 --> 14:11.591
| just want chips.

14:11.601 --> 14:13.137
Jack, you're eating
too much junk.

14:13.145 --> 14:14.555
You got to eat something real.

14:14.563 --> 14:17.726
Hello? Chips are,
like, potatoes.

14:20.652 --> 14:24.270
[ Police radio chatter]

14:24.281 --> 14:27.944
Mom... where are we going?

14:39.963 --> 14:41.373
[Church bells tolling]

14:41.381 --> 14:43.463
Emily?
I really appreciate this.

14:43.467 --> 14:45.082
Emily:
Oh, don't mention it.

14:45.510 --> 14:47.842
Nick is so excited
Jack's joining us today.

14:47.846 --> 14:49.507
You boys should go in.

14:49.514 --> 14:51.254
Pastor Dan's leading Bible study
this morning,

14:51.266 --> 14:53.097
and he doesn't like
tardy teens.

14:53.101 --> 14:54.477
He's welcome to spend the day.

14:54.478 --> 14:56.093
[Cellphone ringing] Pick
him up whenever you like.

14:56.104 --> 14:58.481
Just no later than 8:00.
It's a school night.

15:00.609 --> 15:03.146
Thanks again.
I'll call you later.

15:03.153 --> 15:04.734
Yeah.

15:08.241 --> 15:09.947
It's the best I could do.
Sorry.

15:09.951 --> 15:11.737
You'll be safe here.

15:11.745 --> 15:13.701
Safe from what?

15:15.165 --> 15:16.245
Have fun.

15:16.249 --> 15:18.956
I'll pick you up
in a few hours.

15:23.340 --> 15:26.127
[Siren walls]

15:37.521 --> 15:40.012
The DA's looking to fry
your ass, Belko.

15:43.568 --> 15:46.150
So if you got anything to say,
now's the time to say it.

15:51.493 --> 15:53.950
You hear?

16:00.961 --> 16:03.873
Why you did it.

16:08.051 --> 16:10.337
Hell, I would have, too.

16:16.393 --> 16:19.806
A man can only take so much,
right?

16:21.022 --> 16:23.308
Bev never letting up.

16:24.151 --> 16:26.437
And there comes Richmond...

16:28.655 --> 16:31.943
Killing that sweet little girl.

16:32.701 --> 16:35.283
If that was me, whew.

16:36.455 --> 16:39.538
I would have gone
for the head shot.

16:41.501 --> 16:43.492
Make a statement.

16:46.006 --> 16:48.497
Hey.

16:48.508 --> 16:52.171
You ain't no killer, Belko.

16:54.014 --> 16:56.676
Just trying to make it right.

16:57.476 --> 16:59.842
Right?

16:59.853 --> 17:02.344
The world.

17:02.355 --> 17:03.686
Everything in it.

17:04.733 --> 17:06.314
[Sniffles]

17:06.318 --> 17:08.900
| feel you.

17:09.946 --> 17:12.688
I do.

17:12.699 --> 17:13.779
[Sniffles]

17:13.783 --> 17:15.865
Hey, look at me.

17:15.869 --> 17:18.986
Belko, look at me.

17:20.040 --> 17:21.826
Look at me.

17:25.295 --> 17:29.004
You're not the only one
that knows you did right.

17:31.092 --> 17:33.424
He's here?

17:33.428 --> 17:36.170
He knows?

17:38.558 --> 17:41.925
Yeah. Sure. He knows.

17:41.937 --> 17:44.269
'Cause l-l got to tell him...

17:44.648 --> 17:46.684
I got to tell him why, okay?

17:46.691 --> 17:48.898
I got to tell Stan why.

17:48.902 --> 17:50.438
- Okay?
- Okay.

17:50.445 --> 17:51.525
- Okay.
- Yeah.

17:51.530 --> 17:53.236
- Okay. I got to tell him.
- Yeah.

17:53.240 --> 17:54.605
Okay.

17:54.616 --> 17:56.823
[Sniffles]

17:59.454 --> 18:00.569
Boys are ready.

18:00.580 --> 18:02.195
I told them you were going
down to the warehouse.

18:02.207 --> 18:04.198
Good. I'll meet you
at the diner

18:04.209 --> 18:06.245
after I go see Belko.

18:08.838 --> 18:11.090
Don't be blaming yourself
for that, Stan.

18:11.424 --> 18:13.335
You couldn't have known.

18:13.343 --> 18:15.049
[Sighs]

18:15.804 --> 18:18.011
Denny's been asking
about Mitch.

18:18.348 --> 18:20.384
I told him that she was going
to my mom's house,

18:20.392 --> 18:22.178
but I don't think
that he believed me.

18:22.185 --> 18:24.050
What are we gonna tell
them, Stan?

18:24.062 --> 18:25.927
Have you heard from her yet?

18:27.607 --> 18:28.938
Maybe you should call her.

18:28.942 --> 18:30.603
Well, did you at least
leave a message?

18:30.610 --> 18:32.692
Yeah, like a hundred of them.

18:32.696 --> 18:34.277
[ Footsteps]

18:34.281 --> 18:37.148
Finally, you're ready.

18:37.158 --> 18:38.659
I'm starving. Let's go.

18:38.660 --> 18:40.025
Where's mom, dad?

18:40.036 --> 18:41.901
Put your hat on, buddy.
It's cold out there.

18:41.913 --> 18:43.119
What are you boys
gonna order? Let's go.

18:43.123 --> 18:44.158
There they are!
[ Indistinct shouting ]

18:44.165 --> 18:45.701
Miss, miss, did you
know Belko Royce

18:45.709 --> 18:47.199
was going to shoot
Rosie's killer?!

18:47.210 --> 18:49.417
Terry, get them inside!

18:52.090 --> 18:53.375
Okay, go upstairs.

18:53.383 --> 18:55.089
Go upstairs. Go upstairs.
Go upstairs.

18:55.093 --> 18:58.210
[ Indistinct shouting
continues ]

19:03.059 --> 19:07.302
Go home, take a nap.
I'll stay.

19:07.897 --> 19:11.264
No, no. You go.
You should go.

19:13.820 --> 19:16.778
You should have seen him
last night.

19:17.198 --> 19:21.316
He was on fire.
They loved him.

19:22.871 --> 19:24.827
Where were you?

19:26.458 --> 19:29.621
Something I ate...
my stomach...

19:30.337 --> 19:32.419
I'm not sure.

19:34.633 --> 19:37.670
Don't you have a cat
to feed or something?

19:37.677 --> 19:39.463
I thought you had a pet.

19:39.471 --> 19:41.587
I had a goldfish once.

19:41.598 --> 19:42.758
Too much commitment.

19:42.766 --> 19:44.222
Oh.

19:44.225 --> 19:47.217
So I guess a girlfriend's
out of the picture.

19:47.228 --> 19:49.890
Yeah. Relationships
are too much work.

19:49.898 --> 19:52.640
Better to be a garden-variety
asexual, you know?

19:52.651 --> 19:53.731
[ Laughs softly]

19:54.486 --> 19:57.523
I should try that.

20:02.327 --> 20:04.693
Was he faithful to her?

20:10.960 --> 20:14.202
It all makes sense.

20:14.214 --> 20:16.205
He loved her.

20:24.808 --> 20:26.673
[ Police radio chatter]

20:31.481 --> 20:33.688
I'm looking for
Lieutenant Gil Sloane.

20:33.692 --> 20:34.852
He worked a narc job

20:34.859 --> 20:36.975
that intersects with a drug bust
I'm on for the city.

20:36.986 --> 20:39.147
Lieutenant Sloane retired
two months ago.

20:39.531 --> 20:41.647
You got a number
I could catch him at?

20:41.658 --> 20:43.694
You'll have to talk
to my lieutenant.

